title: TO DO: Dressed up dogs in Jupiter, zombies in Delray
text:
JUPITER
Trick or doggy treats
Get the pup dressed up and get down to the Friends of Jupiter Beach 1st Annual Barks & Beaches Fundraiser that will be held 10 a.m. to 4 p.m. today at Abacoa Town Center in Jupiter. The event will celebrate the 21st Anniversary of Friends of Jupiter Beach with food, children’s activities, music, vendors, a dog wash, doggie Halloween costume contest, free bicycle helmets for kids, pet adoptions, and more. Free. 1200 Town Center Drive. www.barksandbeaches.com
LAKE WORTH
“It’s Academic!”
The Symphonic Band of the Palm Beaches is kicking off its 55th season with “It’s Academic!” at 7:30 p.m. tonight at the Duncan Theatre at Palm Beach State College Lake Worth Campus. The band will welcome special guests the Florida Gulf Coast University Wind Orchestra. The concert’s musical selections will take listeners on a memorable journey through Russia, Japan, France, Greece, Peru’s Machu Picchu and back to the USA. $18. 4200 S. Congress Ave. 561-832-3115; www.SymphonicBand.org
WELLINGTON
Treats from the trunk
Returning for its seventh-straight year the Trunk or Treat Event: A Safe Alternative to Trick or Treating will be held from 3 to 5 p.m. today at Wellington Community High School . Volunteers will decorate their vehicles and distribute Halloween treats to ages 10 and under out of their trunks. Free. 2101 Greenview Shores Blvd. 561-795-4919; susan.may@palmbeachschools.org
DELRAY BEACH
A night to dismember!
Enjoy the ‘deadest’ party in Delray from 10 p.m. to 1 a.m. tonight at 1985 ZOMBIE PROM at the Delray Beach Center for the Arts/Vintage Gymnasium . The party will include a Zombie DJ spinning classic 80’s tunes all night, Zombie Art Sale, lounge area for those feeling “less lively,” crowning of Zombie Prom King and Queen, couples photos, and cash bar. $20. 51 N. Swinton Ave. 561-243-7922; www.DelrayArts.org
